2. The combination of claim 1, wherein the base has a bottom wall, a front wall, and a pair of sidewalls; the bottom wall of the base having a front edge disposed opposite of the hinge; 
wherein the lid has an upper wall, a front wall, and a pair of sidewalls; and 
the lock reception cavity being defined intermediate the bottom wall and the upper wall.

7. A key for unlocking a lock from a media storage container; the key comprising: 
a base; 
at least one key pin projecting from the base; the key pin having a length; 
a movable portion having an opening aligned with the key pin; 
the movable portion being movable between resting and depressed positions; a substantial portion of the length of each key pin projecting through the movable portion when the movable portion is in the depressed; and 
a substantial portion of the length of the key pin being behind the movable portion when the movable portion is in the resting position.

11. A media storage container and lock for locking the storage container; the combination comprising: 
a media storage container having a base and a lid; 
the lid connected to the base with a hinge and movable between open and closed positions; 
the base having a base front wall disposed opposite from the hinge; 
the lid having a lid front wall disposed opposite from the hinge; 
the lid front wall and base front wall being overlapped when the lid is in the closed position such that one of the front walls is disposed inwardly of the other front wall; 
the front walls defining locking finger openings that are aligned when the lid is in the closed position; 
a lock selectively attachable to the container; the lock being in a locked position when attached to the container; 
the lock including a first hooked locking finger; 
the first hooked locking finger being disposed in the aligned locking finger holes of the front walls when the lock is in the locked position; and 
the first hooked locking finger preventing the lid from opening and preventing the lock from being removed from the locked position.

16. A media storage container and lock for locking the storage container; the combination comprising: 
a media storage container having a base and a lid; 
the lid connected to the base with a hinge and movable between open and closed positions; 
the base having a base front wall disposed opposite from the hinge; 
the base having base sidewalls connected to the base front wall to define base corners; 
the lid having a lid front wall disposed opposite from the hinge; 
the lid having lid sidewalls connected to the lid front wall to define lid corners; 
the lid front wall and base front wall being overlapped when the lid is in the closed position such that the lid front wall is disposed inwardly of the base front wall; 
the front walls defining openings that are aligned when the lid is in the closed position; 
a lock selectively attachable to the container; the lock being in a locked position when attached to the container; 
the lock including a first lock member; 
the first lock member being disposed in the aligned openings of the front walls when the lock is in the locked position; and 
the base including corner walls spaced from the base corners; the base corners and the corner walls defining a channel that receives the lid corners when the lid is in the closed position.
